Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significantly elevated creatinine, proteinuria, glycosuria, and ketonuria, suggesting acute or chronic renal dysfunction with possible tubular involvement. Urine is dilute with low specific gravity and abnormal appearance. HbA1c is unexpectedly low despite glycosuria, possibly due to anemia or recent changes in glucose control. No evidence of urinary infection. Recommend further nephrological and diabetic evaluation, and assessment for possible acute kidney injury or underlying chronic kidney disease.
